Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane has found that President Cyril Ramaphosa misled parliament over his response to a donation from Bosasa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the media on Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane's report on Sunday. Mkhwebane found Ramaphosa deliberately misled Parliament about money he received from Bosasa for his ANC presidential campaign. READ: Ramaphosa misled Parliament on Bosasa donation: Mkhwebane She says Parliament's Ethics Committee should decide on a sanction for the President. But, he's not an MP. READ: PP's findings: President maintains innocence Ramaphosa initially said the R500, 000 payment was made to his son for services rendered. He later retracted the answer and clarified that it was a donation to his ANC presidential campaign. The president will address the nation at 18:00pm tonight at the Union Buildings.